I love this game, but there are some problems. For one the AI will always gang up on the player even if you custom make teams, for example 2v2v2v2 the player will be attacked far more often than their AI teammate regardless of positioning. Also double income only affects AI. Finally, multiplayer has a problem, because there isn't a spectator option you have to hope the host is considerate and chooses a map that will allow everyone in the lobby to play otherwise some people will be forced to watch. [Edit] Thank you for adding spectator mode next update but shouldn't that mean that the host now has to pick a map able to hold everyone that isn't spectating, I mean it only makes sense. Also, as for the AI I guess i'm just unlucky, however I still love the game!
replyContent: The AI doesn't ever check if another team is an AI or player, but might attack a team more often that has more units and buildings. The next update does have a spectator mode, but that doesn't change much with host's picking bad maps.

replyContent: If they leave you can control their units. If it's just afk that's tricky, I might look at adding an afk timer that turns on shared control for them. Edit: Shared control is a match setting the host can set (can be fun with friends). But you can override it for yourself by typing '-share off' in chat, the server should reply saying it off for you.

The developers need to somehow reinvent these two controls to work together for better gameplay.

This borrows heavily from the command and conquer, total annihilation games from the late 90's. It recreates the feel brilliantly. Unfortunately those games required a large amount of micro management of upgrades, units, combinations etc. The simplest way we used to handle this was reduce the speed of the game. A fully featured RTS game for Mobile? Yes, Yes and Yes!  The last RTS I remember playing on Android was Starcraft via Emulation back sometime 2013 (Winulator, anyone?). I see this game has existed for quite some time prior, but only recently came across it.  I've only played a couple Skirmish maps so far, and it's actually really enjoyable! Need I mention this has Multiplayer? I can't wait to get my Nephew a copy of this so we can play this when I visit! (We'd play aomx (another RTS) often when we used to live close)  Some may argue the GFX are terrible, but I disagree. Sure, it gives off that 1996 look, but that gives it charm! it's a very smooth experience you need to see in motion!  As far as I know, there are no Population caps, so go wild with Units! Some users claim there aren't enough maps, well.. The community's got ya covered!  I've never played Total Annihilation, or much C&C outside of a Demo, but for someone who's only played AoE 1&2&M and Starcraft to draw experiences from, I feel quite at home with this game! Well worth it!

Again, I love this game, but it's certainly not for everyone.

Really love this game and where it is going, it started out relatively simple (in comparison to now) and now we severs for online play as well as the ability to watch replays of multi-player games. It is a great rts staying true to the roots of genre defining titles such a 'C&C' and 'Supreme Commander'. I have a couple of suggestions though, looking through replays, most of games involve spamming up lots of either hover tanks or gunships (as well as mass amounts of fabricators). This is sad as other units are neglected. To combat this, how about making a second resource in the game like power. You could start of with say, 10 power, this will allow you to build engineers and construct a simple base. To build a army, the player would need to build expensive 'power generators' that increases the total power by X amount. Bigger units such as bombers and gunships could use 2 power units each. Units such as experimental's would cost considerably more, power generators could also have a t2 upgrade to double the output. This would make the player have to think about how they will attack and balance their power at the same time, rather than building mass amount of units and just sending them to a enemy base. Also (to keep the balance) fabricators could also cost a reasonable amount of power, this will prevent people just spamming fabricators and then power generators. I hope you really consider implementing these features as I think it would really improve the multi-player element of the game, thanks for reading.
replyContent: I agree some of the balance needs to be changed up to allow other units to be used more. Are you playing on 1.11p3? Hovertanks have been nerfed in that version they still being spammed? Light or heavy hovertanks? I am looking into power, not sure about setting it up like that for the high tier units, people would then likely spam basic units.

Suggestion for next big update: Stealth. Requires Tier 3 Factories to build, either they can get closer to a turret/target without being detected, or they take less hits when fired at (ie a T3 turret finds them, but every 3rd shot doesn't count against their health). This app is fantastic and well-executed. It's not only addicting, it also gives you a feel of strategy.    The A.I in this is well-balanced. When the A.I level is at easy, they tend to get weak. The replay value is wonderful. You have not just the mission or skirmish,  it also have varieties of game modes which makes this app stand out.   The artstyle is brilliant. The graphics is colorful and attractive that you won't get tired of seeing it. The screen qualities is impressive and well-balanced that it's not too blurry or color distracting.  However, I have a criticism I need to address. There's a lack of picking color options for your player faction. It gets very bored by playing just green. I request that you add option of picking colors for the player faction like red, blue, purple, etc.   Overall, this app is excellent and well-done. Keep up a good work.  P.S.- I heard from one of Youtube video that you're adding bug faction. I request that you add more faction to make the factions more varied.

content: I didn't know there were games like this on the phone... I could sit back and build turrets, AA, and never come under real threat. When I wanted to end the round I would build a fleet of helicopters that could decimate whatever stood their way. Like I said, it was enjoyable but would like to see the frame of the game improved.

content: Its good to see a programmer just out to make games that people enjoy. No annoying ads, no bloody payments inside the game itself. Just a one off fee and a classic and FUN game. I'd gladly pay a few pounds for a decent multiplayer RTS without all the ad crap or in game expenses..  Good work Corroding Games!
replyContent: Glad you like the game, yeah I stick to what I want as a gamer. So no ads, no drm, no pay to win, etc. Yeah a chatroom for the lobby would be quite useful, and I agree the multiplayer interface needs some improvements.

replyContent: That sounds quite bad, does it give you the option of sending a crash report when it crashes? I haven't seen any mid-game crash reports like that. Would love to get this fixed, feel free to send me an email if you have any details. I might also need to add auto saving as well to help in the meantime.

content: Pretty good RTS game, i just wish there were a few more minor controls such as clicking on the minimap to scroll over, and better grouping. As of now i cant seem to delete a group or take units out of one. But overall fun and i guess worth the money
replyContent: Glad you like the game. To scroll with the minimap you need to hold press if you have units selected (otherwise they get a move order there instead). And to replace or delete a group, you need to hold down the group button for about 2 seconds, otherwise the group will just added to. I need to work on making this stuff more clear in-game.

content: Quite good

Is good, especially multiplayer but the current connection process is tedious.  Please make it simpler to establish a multiplayer connection over Wi-fi.  No IP address nonsense, just detect any games hosted on the local network.  Better still, enable online handles so that you can favourite other users to do a quick game.  Look at Swing Shot's intuitive handshake process for inspiration.  It annoys me that multiplayer mode can't detect when you've defeated you're opponent.  You have to agree with them to stop the game even if every unit is dead.  Needs some sort of sound effect to indicate when you're under attack the red cross on the map is not enough.  Can you fade the ground scars after a while ? It gets hard to see units when the ground is full of craters.  A capture the flag mode would be good to.
replyContent: The new update shows multiplayer games both on LAN, and online, so should improve that connection process quite a bit. I'll work on fixing your other issues. And can you email me how your capture the flag idea would work, seems interesting but I haven't seen that mode in an RTS.

replyContent: I know this is old, but I can only just reply to comments :) Just letting you know you can save and load games, this has been in the game for a few version now. Just press the option menu in-game and click save game. You can even save multiplayer games now, so you can continue a game with a friend over a few lunch breaks :)

content: Was looking for an RTS like this. Can't wait to see what else the developer has planned!
Yes! This is the rts I was looking for! Takes me back to the early days of rts. Not fancy graphics, but very fun. Works great on my Galaxy S 4g.

If u want a red alert type game this is ur thing. No need to spend money on pc game of this type bevuz this is all u need. GAME is not that hard if u are experienced in these types of games but definitely a slight challenge and has GREAT potential.

By far the most well designed rts of its type; no pay to play nonsense, no annoying ads, etc. I searched awhile to find this gem (btw for the gaming powers that be I will never, ever play a gaming ap that requires real money to progress within the game).  The control interface here is almost flawless, very intuitive for fans of the genre, visuals are clean if not spare, and the game offers a healthy diversity of units. I would echo other slight complaints:  It's far too easy, and could use added complexity.

It keeps getting updates making it better and keeping me coming back for more, usually for hours and hours at a time. If the game gets a couple more maps every month I'll be really happy. AI could use some work to make it more challenging, really the biggest issue right now.

Well with the $3 I paid. Just like the good old days of c&c!      A few things I would like to see changed though... it seems you can only do one game saved at once. I cant do the campaign then start a survival with out losing my saved campaign. This something I would love to see fixed.    more units and improved graphics would also be nice  Although still a grwat game any rts fan will enjoy it!
